This paper deals with interval temporal logics, which are commonly studied in the field of logic (cs.LO). It also involves complexity analysis and decidability, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper uses mathematical techniques such as classification and analysis, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with fragments of a logic, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
